Property Rights
PS, Scarcity Rent, and Long-Run Competitive Equilibrium

In the short-run, \[
\overbrace{PS}^{\text{Producer}\\\,\text{ Surplus}} \,=\, \overbrace{\Pi}^{\text{Profits}} + \overbrace{FC}^{\text{Fixed}\\\,\text{Cost}}
\]
This is because: \[
\begin{align}
\overbrace{\Pi}^{\text{Profits}} &\,=\, \overbrace{TR}^{\text{Total Revenue}} \,‚Äì\, \overbrace{VC}^{\text{Variable}\\\;\;\text{Cost}} \,‚Äì\, \overbrace{FC}^{\text{Fixed}\\\,\text{Cost}}\\
\quad\\
\underbrace{PS}_{\text{Producer}\\\,\text{ Surplus}} &\,=\, \underbrace{TR}_{\text{Total Revenue}} \,‚Äì\, \underbrace{VC}_{\text{Variable}\\\;\;\text{Cost}}
\end{align}
\]
Thus, \(PS \,=\, \Pi + FC\) in the short-run.
